With the damage visible, one can’t say the recent natural disaster is water under the bridge. Durban residents are still forced to negotiate their city’s collapsed infrastructure. It has become part of everyday life. But their premier, Sihle Zikalala, has promised to do more to prepare for severe weather in the future. eNCA contributor Mpho Lakaje brings us this feature from Durban. #DStv403 DURBAN - Weeks after KwaZulu-Natal was battered by severe floods, the province continues to rebuild. Premier Sihle Zikalala announced a few days ago that the death toll has now risen to 461 wile 87 others remain unaccounted for. READ: KZN floods | Pipelines to take a year to repair Meanwhile, damage to infrastructure is valued at R25-billion. Zikalala has vowed to implement short and long-term measures to mitigate future disasters. * eNCA contributor Mpho Lakaje reports.